               <p>THE HONOURABLE LORD ASHLEY. On the 20th of April, about two o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18260511-104-crimeloc618">Great Maddox-street, St. George's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260511-104-crimeloc618" type="placeName" value="Great Maddox-street, St. George's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260511-104-crimeloc618" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260511-104-off614 t18260511-104-crimeloc618"></join>, and felt a pull at my right-hand coat pocket, which made me turn round, and I saw the prisoner endeavouring to get my handkerchief into his hand - he passed me, and ran in front. I know it to be my handkerchief - I had used it ten minutes before. I took him to the office.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260511-104-person629">
